ZCZC GE94
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 062300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE
CENTRED ACROSS THE NETHERLANDS 1004 WITH AN AREA OF HIGH
PRESSURE CENTRED 250 MILES W OF FITZROY 1029. DURING
WEDNESDAY THE LOW IS EXP TO TRACK NWARDS TO BECOME
CENTRED FISHER 1003 BY MIDDAY. BY MIDDAY THURSDAY THE LOW
IS THEN EXP TO HAVE MOVD AWAY NE TO BE NERN SWEDEN 1001
WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE FLW ACROSS THE N SEA.
ANOTHER ATLANTIC LOW IS THEN EXP TO DEVELOP AND MOV
EWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED FAIR ISLE 993 BY EARLY AFTERNOON
ON FRIDAY AND THEN TO JUST N OF THE SHETLAND ISLANDS BY
EVENING. ON TUESDAY NIGHT STRG WINDS WILL DEVELOP WITH
GALES POSSIBLY AFFECTING FORTIES DOGGER FISHER AND
GERMAN BIGHT FOR A TIME ON WEDNESDAY THEN EASING TO STRG
BY EVENING. STRG WINDS WILL AFFECT MOST WATERS ON
THURSDAY AND DURING FRIDAY SW WINDS MAY INCREASE TO GALE
ACROSS SOME CENTRAL AREAS
